## Streaming

Data transfer in real time in response to some event



## Input Stream

# for exposing file on localsystem via netcat
#This command will provide text through localhost:8088 for the first user which accesess it

cat data/sample1.txt | nc -l 8088


## output stream
# outputting stream to some file system, dashboard, console etc

# invoked using spark.writeStream



## Windowing

# run spark queries within a time window.
# The time should be in ISO format. e.g. datetime.datetime.now().isoformat()


## Write mode

# For aggregate data: complete, update
# for non aggregate data: append

